{0 How to add a CSS stylesheet?}

{e Warning: css_link and make_uri come from Eliom.Content.Html.D module. This module is opened for each piece of code}

CSS stylesheet are included in the header using the {b css_link} function.

{@ocaml[
css_link
     ~uri:(make_uri (Eliom.Service.static_dir ())
              ["css";"style.css"])
     ()
]}
This function has 2 parameters: the file path and unit.

The file path is generated using the {b make_uri} function. This function creates the relative URL string using the static directory configured in the configuration file and the given list.

{2 Where?}

Insert this piece of code on the list given in parameter to the {b head} function:

{@ocaml[
  (html
     (head (title (txt "Page Title"))
        [css_link ~uri:(make_uri (Eliom.Service.static_dir ())
	        	  ["css";"style.css"]) ()])
     (body [p [txt "Hello World!"]]))))
]}

Or you can use:
{!Eliom.Tools.F.head}



